begin
reserve n for Nat;
reserve K for Field;
reserve M1 for (Matrix of n,K);
theorem
(n > ( 0 ) implies (M1 is  Idempotent iff ( M1 @ ) is  Idempotent))
proof
assume A1: n > ( 0 );
set M2 = ( M1 @ );
A2: (( width M1 ) = n & ( len M1 ) = n) by MATRIX_1:24;
thus (M1 is  Idempotent implies M2 is  Idempotent)
proof
assume A3: M1 is  Idempotent;
( M2 * M2 ) = ( ( M1 * M1 ) @ ) by A1,A2,MATRIX_3:22
.= M2 by A3,CKB1:def 1;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;

A4: (( width M2 ) = n & ( len M2 ) = n) by MATRIX_1:24;
assume A5: M2 is  Idempotent;
M1 = ( M2 @ ) by A1,A2,MATRIX_2:13
.= ( ( M2 * M2 ) @ ) by A5,CKB1:def 1
.= ( ( M2 @ ) * ( M2 @ ) ) by A1,A4,MATRIX_3:22
.= ( M1 * ( ( M1 @ ) @ ) ) by A1,A2,MATRIX_2:13
.= ( M1 * M1 ) by A1,A2,MATRIX_2:13;
hence thesis by CKB1:def 1;
end;
